---
description: Guide pandas open-source contributions using stage commands and shared core rules
alwaysApply: true
---

When the user is working on a pandas contribution:

1. Follow global invariants in `.cursor/skills/pandas-contribution-core/SKILL.md`.
2. Use the matching stage command or skill for the current step — do not run the full workflow unless asked:
   - `/pandas-start` — intake + clarify change
   - `/pandas-inspect` — inspect local context
   - `/pandas-plan` — risk + test-first plan
   - `/pandas-implement` — scaffold minimal change
   - `/pandas-verify` — checks + PR readiness (auto-continues to ship on success)
   - `/pandas-ship` — PR package + role handoffs
   - `/pandas-full` — full demo flow
3. Do not select issues automatically. Assume the user has already chosen an issue or change.
4. Start by clarifying the change before proposing code edits.
5. Search local repo docs first. Use online docs only to fill gaps. If local and online docs conflict, prefer the local checkout.
